<section id="about" class="py-24 px-6">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-8 text-center">Who's behind this</h2>
    <div class="bg-white/[0.03] border border-white/[0.06] rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-10">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-center md:items-start">
        <img
          src="/og-image.png"
          alt="Greg Knoblauch"
          class="w-32 h-32 rounded-full object-cover shrink-0"
        />
        <div>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            I'm Greg — a software engineer by day, network nerd by choice. I've spent over 8 years building backend systems and cloud infrastructure professionally, and somewhere along the way I started applying that same mindset to home networks.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            It started with my own place — I wanted proper coverage, segmented devices, local camera storage, and gear that didn't phone home to some manufacturer's cloud. Once I had it dialled in, friends and neighbours started asking for the same thing.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            ProperNet is how I turn that into a service. I design and install networks using the same enterprise-grade hardware and practices I'd use in a professional environment — just scaled for homes, offices, and small businesses in Edmonton.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">
            Want to know more? Check out my personal site at
            <a href="https://gkno.ca" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent hover:underline">gkno.ca</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
